    "created_at": "2015-08-06T16:56:42Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-08-06T16:56:42Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "There is is no good answer here. Servers listen on specific ports, and sometimes servers listen on specific ports but only on specific addresses. To cover the most general case, we need to take an addr parameter, but conceptually, this is telling the server what to listen on, and calling that an addr would be worse than calling that a port. We could name it grpc_server_add_[secure_]http2_addr_and_port, but I am not sure if this is better than just relying on comments and type checking to ensure correct usage. \n"
